# Error Handling

DocuVault uses standardized error responses for consistent client-side handling.

## Error Response Format
```typescript
interface ErrorResponse {
  success: false;
  error: {
    code: string;
    message: string;
    details?: any;
  };
}
```

## Common Error Codes
| Code               | Description                                     |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------- |
| `validation_error` | Invalid input parameters                        |
| `not_found`        | Requested resource not found                    |
| `unauthorized`     | User not authenticated or session invalid       |
| `forbidden`        | User does not have permission for the operation |
| `blockchain_error` | Error interacting with the blockchain           |
| `server_error`     | Internal server error                           |

## Best Practices
- Always check the `success` property to determine if the request succeeded
- Handle specific error codes appropriately in the UI
- Provide user-friendly error messages based on error codes

